title: Rangers take lead on bizarre play in Game 5 of ALDS
text: Rangers take lead on bizarre play in Game 5 of ALDS The Associated Press The Associated Press The Associated Press The Associated Press The Associated Press Home plate umpire Dale Scott, left, signals for Texas Rangers' Rougned Odor to score after conferring with the base umpires to confirm an error by Toronto Blue Jays catcher Russell Martin (not shown) on the play during the seventh inning in Game 5 of baseball's American League Division Series, Wednesday, Oct. 14, 2015 in Toronto. (Frank Gunn/The Canadian Press via AP) MANDATORY CREDIT Toronto Blue Jays manager John Gibbons argues with the umpires after a call during the seventh inning in Game 5 of baseball's American League Division Series against the Texas Rangers, Wednesday, Oct. 14, 2015 in Toronto. (Nathan Denette/The Canadian Press via AP) MANDATORY CREDIT Texas Rangers' Rougned Odor celebrates with teammates after scoring on an error Toronto Blue Jays catcher Russell Martin (not shown) during the seventh inning in Game 5 of baseball's American League Division Series, Wednesday, Oct. 14, 2015 in Toronto. (Frank Gunn/The Canadian Press via AP) MANDATORY CREDIT Texas Rangers' Rougned Odor, left, celebrates with Prince Fielder after scoring a run during the seventh inning in Game 5 of baseball's American League Division Series against the Toronto Blue Jays, Wednesday, Oct. 14, 2015 in Toronto. (Nathan Denette/The Canadian Press via AP) MANDATORY CREDIT A grounds crew member collects beer cans thrown on to the field after the Texas Rangers scored a run during the seventh inning in Game 5 of baseball's American League Division Series, Wednesday, Oct. 14, 2015 in Toronto. (Nathan Denette/The Canadian Press via AP) MANDATORY CREDIT By The Associated Press
